<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1438,951,1301]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1060,1085]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be distinguished from its congeners by: 1) head sparsely punctate, interspaces between 2–3 punctures’ diameters, with a median longitudinal region ca. 
<quantity box="[1034,1126,1095,1120]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
width; 2) antennomere II distinctly longer than III; 3) admedian row of pronotum consisting of 7–8 punctures; lateral row, curvedly arranged, of 7–8 punctures; 4) anterior angle of pronotum not protruding, but rounded; 5) mesoscutellum shallowly covered with transverse microstriae; 5) each side of elytra bearing 8–9 rows of punctures; 6) interspaces between punctures on abdomen of 3–4 punctures’ diameter; 7) median lobe of aedeagus elliptical, inner sac membranous and dilated towards apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
